<p><strong>Staff of the Avatar</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Colossal Weapons" href="/Colossal+Weapons">Colossal Weapon</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Staff of the Avatar</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity">Dexterity</a>, and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith">Faith</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for those who want a STR/FAI hybrid melee build.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Ceremonial staff depicting the Erdtree in its historic radiance. Wielded by the avatars who protect the Minor Erdtrees.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The avatars, emerging in the wake of the Elden Ring's shattering, were determined to protect the withering Erdtree's offspring.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Staff of the Avatar in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Staff of the Avatar weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Drops from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Erdtree Avatar" href="/Erdtree+Avatar">Erdtree Avatar</a>&nbsp;you encounter near the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1889&amp;lat=-169.42813&amp;lng=132.71962&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1889&amp;lat=-169.42813&amp;lng=132.71962&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB">Great Waterfall Crest</a> site of grace. 
  <ul> 
   <li>To reach the area, you can either: 
    <ul> 
     <li>Defeat the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Valiant Gargoyle" href="/Valiant+Gargoyle">Valiant Gargoyle</a> duo boss in the Siofra Aqueduct, then lie down on the coffin at the back of the arena. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=5452&amp;lat=-103.4&amp;lng=123.6&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB" href="/Interactive+Map?id=5452&amp;lat=-103.4&amp;lng=123.6&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
     <li>Pass through two consecutive hidden walls in the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Frenzied Flame Proscription" href="/Frenzied+Flame+Proscription">Frenzied Flame Proscription</a>, then carefully descend down the roots and cliffs to the ground.</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>After entering the Deeproot Depths, <a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/bnPctEycShs?t=1380">Video Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Staff of the Avatar Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Erdtree Slam" href="/Erdtree+Slam">Erdtree Slam</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Staff of the Avatar</strong>&nbsp;can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>This staff is the signature one <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Erdtree Avatar" href="/Erdtree+Avatar">Erdtree Avatars</a> use all throughout the game.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">500</li> 
 <li>1092 dmg on +10 with 99 all stats, highest from all unique weapons.</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
